At level 25, each wisdom under 200= 5 mana<br>
                each wisdom over 200 = 1 mana<br>
At level 50, each wisdom under 200 = 10 mana<br>
                each wisdom over 200 = 1 mana<br>
At level 60, each wisdom under 200 = 12 mana<br>
                each wisdom over 200 = 1 mana<br>
<br>
How it is now:<br>
At level 25, each wisdom under 200 = 5 mana<br>
                each wisdom over 200 = 2.5 mana<br>
At level 50, each wisdom under 200 = 10 mana<br>
                each wisdom over 200 = 5 mana<br>
At level 60, each wisdom under 200 = 12 mana<br>
                each wisdom over 200 = 6 mana<br>
<br>
This means a lot of things.  Most significantly it means Mana gear is better at low to mid-levels than wisdom.  It would take a 6 wisdom item to equal a 30 mana item at level 25.  So those 35 mana earrings are much better than forest loops.  It also means that Mana gear can be better at high levels if you already have over 200 wisdom.<br>
<br>
I am level 60 with a 214 wisdom currently.  I use 2ac 35hp 25 mana earrings.  These are superior to forest loops for me.  If I were under 200 wisdom then I would get 36 mana, 3 times 12, from the Forest Loops.  But since I am over 200 wisdom I would only get 18 mana, 3 times 6, from them.  Not only would I have less mana but I would miss out from the nice HP on my current earrings. <p><center>
